The paper proposes an attention module for CNN architectures for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The module is end-to-end trainable, which involves optimization and learning, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the role of attention in amplifying relevant information and suppressing irrelevant or misleading information, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
